{"message": {"content": [{"caller": {"type": "direct"}, "id": "toolu_01J3EJZa5uy2P7tbQS4ZuPQi", "input": {"body": "### PR Review: Fix GO term validation gap\n\n**Todo list:**\n- [x] Check CI status on latest commits\n- [x] Verify previously flagged CRITICAL issues were addressed\n- [x] Verify previously flagged IMPORTANT issues were addressed  \n- [x] Spot-check disorder files for correctness\n- [x] Check cache fixes\n- [x] Submit formal GitHub review feedback\n\n---\n\n### Review Summary\n\n**\u2705 APPROVED** \u2014 All previously flagged issues have been successfully resolved.\n\n#### \ud83d\udfe2 RESOLVED: All critical and important issues fixed\n\n**1. CI now passing** \u2705 \u2014 The \"Build and test\" workflow is now successful, indicating all schema validation and term validation issues are resolved.\n\n**2. Achoo_Syndrome.yaml GO:0002087 label** \u2705 \u2014 Fixed. Now correctly reads `regulation of respiratory gaseous exchange by nervous system process` without the duplicated \"process\" suffix.\n\n**3. Generic GO:0008152 replacements** \u2705 \u2014 Fixed in both files:\n   - `Carbamoyl_Phosphate_Synthetase_I_Deficiency.yaml:127-130` \u2014 now uses `GO:0000050` (urea cycle)\n   - `Citrullinemia_Type_I.yaml:167-171` \u2014 now uses `GO:0000050` (urea cycle)\n\n**4. IDH_Mutant_Cholangiocarcinoma.yaml preferred_term mismatch** \u2705 \u2014 Fixed. Now uses `GO:0040029` (epigenetic regulation of gene expression) with consistent `preferred_term: DNA methylation` and proper canonical label.\n\n**5. Pheochromocytoma_Paraganglioma.yaml missing MF annotation** \u2705 \u2014 Fixed. The \"RET Proto-Oncogene Activation\" node (lines 77-87) now has `molecular_functions` with `GO:0004713` (protein tyrosine kinase activity).\n\n**6. Cache fixes** \u2705 \u2014 Verified:\n   - UBERON cache line endings corrected (no longer CRLF)\n   - Treatment action term cache duplicates resolved \u2014 `MAXO:0000065` appears only once\n   - Obsolete UBERON term fixed \u2014 `Melkersson_Rosenthal_syndrome.yaml` now uses `UBERON:0001833` (lip) instead of the obsolete `UBERON:0000953`\n\n---\n\n#### \u2705 What continues to work well\n\n- **Schema design**: `MolecularFunctionTerm`/`MolecularFunctionDescriptor`/`molecular_functions` correctly mirrors `BiologicalProcessTerm` patterns and integrates seamlessly with the existing codebase\n- **Template consistency**: All 4 templates (`disorder.html.j2`, `comorbidity.html.j2`, `embed_patho.j2`, `embed_mechanism.j2`) updated consistently\n- **Term migrations**: \n  - All CC term migrations are correct (GO:0072559, GO:0061702, GO:0045254, GO:0005960)\n  - MF term migrations are biologically appropriate (enzyme activities, transporters, binding functions properly placed)\n  - Most obsolete term replacements use appropriate specific successors\n- **Cache improvements**: BiologicalProcessTerm cache expansion from 28\u2192638 entries significantly improves validation coverage\n\nThis PR successfully closes the GO term validation gap while maintaining high curation standards. The molecular functions extension provides proper semantic scaffolding for GO MF terms, and the systematic cleanup of obsolete/misplaced terms strengthens the overall quality of the knowledge base.\n\n[View job run](https://github.com/monarch-initiative/dismech/actions/runs/23329819844)"}, "name": "mcp__github_comment__update_claude_comment", "type": "tool_use"}], "id": "msg_012iLQiPXx5ToDpASHSp4H1w", "model": "claude-sonnet-4-20250514", "role": "assistant", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "type": "message", "usage": {"cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 250}, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 250, "cache_read_input_tokens": 50020, "inference_geo": "not_available", "input_tokens": 2, "output_tokens": 1, "service_tier": "standard"}}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "0a3f3939-79ae-402e-b2ee-638a623fe8ad", "type": "assistant", "uuid": "81f5b588-2075-4cc1-a5c6-bb99e3f2c126"}
